<HEADLINE> Nobel Winner Joins Holocaust Fund Board </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, May 1 (Xinhua) -- Nobel Peace Prize winner Elie Wiesel
was today appointed a member of the Executive Board of the Swiss
Special Fund for Holocaust victims.
</P>
<P>
The naming of Wiesel, one of the three members recommended by
the World Jewish Restitution Organization to the executive board,
was approved by the Swiss Federal Council today.
</P>
<P>
The other two are Joseph Burg, a former Israeli minister, and
Avraham Hirshson, an Israeli parliament member.
</P>
<P>
The board of the fund also includes Rolf Bloch, the President
of the Swiss Federation of Jewish Communities, and three other
Swiss members.
</P>
<P>
Three Swiss private banks have pledged to contribute an
additional 65 million Swiss francs (44.8 million U.S. dollars) to
the original 100 million francs (about 68.9 million dollars),
donation by the Swiss National Bank. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
