<BODY>
<HEADLINE> IOC President Sends Presents to World No. 1 Deng </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANCHESTER, England, May 1 (Xinhua) -- International Olympic
Committee President Juan Antonio Samaranch on Thursday sent
presents to Deng Yaping, the world top women player bidding for a
repeat of singles-doubles glories at the 44th World Table Tennis
Championships.
</P>
<P>
Samaranch's representative, Gilbert Felli, handed a Swiss watch
and a jewellery box to Deng, who has become a member of the IOC
athletes' commission on the recommendation of the Olympic chief.
</P>
<P>
Deng Yaping, whose dedication and attitude to the sport is an
example, has won 16 world championship and World Cup titles in her
11-year-long career.
</P>
<P>
The 24-year-old Chinese has also swept four Olympic titles and
Samaranch has twice awarded the Olympic gold to Deng.
</P>
<P>
Deng, who snatched the singles and doubles events in the last
world championships, led the Chinese squad to its 12th Corbillon
Cup for the women's team event on Tuesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
