<HEADLINE> Rafsanjani Denounces Attempt on Tajik </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, May 1 (Xinhua) -- Iranian President Akbar Hashemi
Rafsanjani today deplored the assassination attempt on the life
of Tajik President Emomali Rakhmonov, who suffered a minor leg
injury in a hand grenade explosion Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
In a message to his Tajik counterpart, Rafsanjani expressed the
hope that the Tajik president will recover soon.
</P>
<P>
Iran's Foreign Ministry also condemned the assassination
attempt and expressed hope that the belligerent Tajik sides will
do everything to safeguard the achievements of the peace talks
until national reconciliation is full in place in Tajikistan.
</P>
<P>
The attack occurred in the northern town of Khojand on Wednesday
when the hand grenade was thrown at the president's feet and
exploded as he got out of a car.
</P>
<P>
Two people were killed and 60 others injured in the attack.
</P>
<P>
The attack came at a time when Rakhmonov's hard-line government
has been negotiating a peace settlement with opposition groups
that have been waging civil war since 1992 in the impoverished
Central Asian nation.
</P>
<P>
As a mediator, Iran had provided offices and other facilities
for the peace talks between the Tajik government and the
opposition group in the past few months. 
</P>
</TEXT>
