<HEADLINE> International Labor Day Marked in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 1 (Xinhua) -- The international Labor Day was
celebrated today by working people of various ethnic groups
throughout China.
</P>
<P>
In the Chinese capital city of Beijing, nearly 150,000 people
watched the raising of the national flag at the Tiananmen Square
this morning. Mass celebrations of various kinds were carried out
in the city's major parks.
</P>
<P>
In Tianjin, the largest port city in north China, the main
streets, parks and recreational centers were decorated with
flowers with art performances on in workers' clubs and cultural
palaces.
</P>
<P>
In Shanghai, China's largest city and economic center in the
east, festivity could be felt everywhere. Workers' activity
centers, clubs, cinemas and theaters in the city were decorated
with lanterns and colored streamers.
</P>
<P>
In southwest China's Chongqing, which was promoted to a
provincial-level municipality in March, up to 10,000 people
gathered at the city's cultural palace to watch art performances,
and sport matches.
</P>
<P>
In Guangzhou, capital of south China's prosperous Guangdong
Province, local people were joined by representatives of trade
unions in Hong Kong to launch various kinds of activities to
welcome the return of Hong Kong to the motherland.
</P>
<P>
In Wuhan, capital of central China's Hubei Province, 600 model
workers marked the festival by continuing their work to build a
new bridge over the Yangtze River.
</P>
<P>
In Urumqi, capital of Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region in
northwest China, recreational activities were held, featuring unity
of all ethnic groups.
</P>
<P>
The May Day was also celebrated in other major Chinese cities,
such as Nanchang, Nanjing, Fuzhou, Xining, Shijiazhuang, Shenyang,
Zhengzhou and Harbin. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
