<HEADLINE> Yeltsin, Albright Have Talks on Telephone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, May 1 (Xinhua) -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin
today expressed satisfaction with the arrival of US Secretary of
State Madeleine Albright to Moscow for talks with Russian Foreign
Minister Yevgeny Primakov.
</P>
<P>
According to the Itar-Tass news agency, the US secretary of
state, who arrived here this morning, in a phone call to Yeltsin
said that the US administration was to adhere to a constructive
dialogue with Russia.
</P>
<P>
The Russian presidential press service said Yeltsin supported
the intention of the Russian and US foreign ministers to
concentrate on main problems which had been discussed at the
Helsinki summit, primarily, on military aspects of European
security.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin meanwhile stressed the importance to prepare a
fundamental document on NATO-Russia relations and, in particular,
to render a concrete meaning to mutual understanding reached at
the Helsinki summit pertaining to non-advancement of NATO military
structures and the adaptation of the CFE Treaty.
</P>
<P>
During the telephone conversation Albright conveied to the
Russian president best regards from US president Bill Clinton, and
convinced Yeltsin of U.S. intention to look for mutual acceptable
way to create security in Europe.  
</P>
</TEXT>
