<HEADLINE> Ethiopian Workers Celebrate International Labour </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, May 1 (Xinhua) -- Workers in the capital today
gathered at Mesquel square here and held a rally to celebrate the
International Labour Day.
</P>
<P>
President of the newly re-organized Confederation of Ethiopian
Trade Unions (CETU) Amare Alemayehu on the occasion called on
Ethiopian workers to make unreserved efforts to consolidate the
newly organized CETU and nurture democracy within its
organizational framework so as to live up to expectations.
</P>
<P>
He said the International Labour Day celebrated annually
worldwide is a living testimony to the struggle waged by the
proletariat for democracy and the respect of human rights.
</P>
<P>
Active involvement of workers in the on-going democratization
process in the country will have its own positive bearing in
changing their life for the better, he said, and assured workers
that CETU will work to its best to ensure the rights of the
workers.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the workers gathering, Ethiopian Minister of
Labour and Social Affairs Hassen Abdella called on workers to
work in unison with the government in its effort to promote
industrialization.
</P>
<P>
Both parties fully exploiting the conducive atmosphere created
for the promotion of productivity and industrial security should
strive to build upon their capabilities to exploit modern
technology, he added.
</P>
<P>
This is the first May Day celebration organized by the newly
re-organized CETU. 
</P>
</TEXT>
