<HEADLINE> Clash in Istanbul "May Day" Rally, 26 Injured </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, May 1 (Xinhua) -- Fifteen policemen and 11
demonstrators were injured in clashes following the "May Day"
rally in Istanbul, the largest city of Turkey, the semi-official
Anatolia News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The clashes broke out when the Turkish security forces tried to
stop the demonstrators who were destroying a bus with stones and
sticks at the Osmanoglu Street of Piyalepasa Boulevard, said the
agency.
</P>
<P>
The agency said that the demonstrators set fire at a bus and a
garbage truck in Okmeydani after the rally, organized by trade
unions of Turk-Is, DISK and KESK, for the celebrations of the "May
Day" in Caglayan Square in Istanbul. Some 100,000 workers attended
the rally.
</P>
<P>
Security forces used tear-gas grenades and opened fire into air
in a bid to disperse a group of about 150 paraders who set fire at
the garbage truck in the place, the report said.
</P>
<P>
Many people were taken under custody in connection with the
clashes between the police and the demonstrators, said the
agency.
</P>
<P>
Demonstrations were held for celebration of "May Day" in
several other large cities such as Ankara and Antalya and ended
peacefully.
</P>
<P>
About 8,000 policemen were on duty today in Istanbul to
prevent possible incidents during the celebrations and the "May
Day" clash last year claimed three lives in the city.
</P>
</TEXT>
