<HEADLINE> Lebanon: No Separation Between Lebanese, </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, May 1 (Xinhua) -- Lebanese Prime Minister Rafik
Al-Hariri reiterated here today that neither Syria nor Lebanon
would sign a separate peace with Israel, noting that the two Arab
states will never yield to threats.
</P>
<P>
Opening the third conference of Cancer in the Middle East,
Al-Hariri held Israel responsible for the current stalemate in the
Middle East peace process, and said that the policy of the Israeli
government leads to the deadlock of its negotiations with Lebanon
and Syria.
</P>
<P>
He asserted that the peace which Lebanon wants is a just and
comprehensive one in the region based on the principle of
exchanging land for peace.
</P>
<P>
