"we together refuse any attempt to separate the Lebanese and
Syrian tracks from any side and under any slogan or initiative. It
is a firm truth and a national decision which can not be discussed
or disputed."
</P>
<P>
"In confronting the continuous Israeli refusal to resume these
negotiations from where they had reached, we state again that the
peace is our strategic choice because Lebanon is a peace-loving
country and denounces aggression," the prime minister underlined.
</P>
<P>
"This peace choice, however, absolutely does not mean that
Lebanon will accept any (separate) peace," he said.
</P>
<P>
"Our another choice is the resistance against the (Israeli)
occupation, with an adherence to a demand of the Israeli
withdrawal from south Lebanon according to U.N. Security Council
Resolution 425," Hariri added.
</P>
<P>
The peace negotiations between Syria and Lebanon on the one
side and Israel on the other have been suspended since the present
Israeli hardline government came to power last year.
</P>
<P>
Damascus demands that the peace talks should be resumed from
where it had reached with the former Israeli government of the
Labor Party. 
