Security Council on the sanctions. Iraq has to destroy all its
chemical, biological weapons and missiles before the council can
decide to lift sanctions.
</P>
<P>
Although Russia, France and some other members argue that
sanctions should be eased in view of the progresses achieved by
Iraq in destroying the massive destructive weapons, the United
States and Britain insist that no change can be made.


