<HEADLINE> UNHCR Begins Repatriating Sierra Leonean Refugees </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, May 1 (Xinhua) -- The U.N. High Commissioner for
Refugees (UNHCR) today began to repatriate 3,046 Sierra Leonean
Refugees in Liberia by sea, air and road, a report reaching here
said.
</P>
<P>
About 1,690 refugees are being transported by sea on three
Sierra Leonean government ships and one UNHCR chartered vessel,
while 200 went home on a UNHCR-chartered flight.
</P>
<P>
About 1,150 refugees on the Sierra Leonean-Liberian
border would return home on foot or by truck.
</P>
<P>
Upon arrival in Sierra Leone, each refugee will be provided
with an assistance package comprising two months' food rations
from the World Food Program, a plastic sheeting, two mats, a
jerrycan, a lamp, a kitchen set and two blankets, a UNHCR
announcement said.
</P>
<P>
Last February, the UNHCR repatriated some 1,200 Sierra Leonean
refugees by sea and another 200 by air.
</P>
<P>
In March, the UNHCR appealed to the donor community for 17
million U.S. Dollars to help repatriate and reintegrate an
estimated 380,000 Sierra Leonean refugees in west Africa.
</P>
