<HEADLINE> US Provides More Funds to Ukraine to Destroy Nuclear </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, May 1 (Xinhua) -- The United States will provide
an additional 47 million U.S. dollars to Ukraine for destroying
the strategic nuclear missiles left by the former Soviet Union,
according to a U.S.-Ukrainian agreement signed today.
</P>
<P>
The agreement was signed by U.S. Defense Secretary William
Cohen and his Ukrainian counterpart, Olexander Kuzmuk, at a
ceremony at the Pentagon. The U.S. has already provided 404
million U.S. dollars to Ukraine.
</P>
<P>
The fund will help Ukraine complete destruction of the SS-19
missiles and begin planning destruction of the more modern SS-24
missiles.
</P>
<P>
Ukraine removed all nuclear warheads from its SS-19 and SS-24
missiles last year.
</P>
<P>
Ukraine was the third-largest nuclear power in the world after
the Soviet Union disintegrated. "The nuclear forces of Ukraine
were composed of the Strategic Rocket Forces and also of the
strategic weapons that were within the air force of Ukraine,"
Kuzmuk told reporters.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a joint briefing with Cohen, Kuzmuk said, "Once we
renounced our nuclear status and once we took upon ourselves...
Ukraine has done so indeed."
</P>
<P>
Ukraine made a "very bold and progressive" decision to
dismantle its strategic nuclear arsenal, Cohen said. "The people
of Ukraine recognize that security comes from constructive
alliances and not from nuclear weapons," he said.
</P>
<P>
Cohen also accepted an invitation from Kuzmuk to visit Ukraine
this summer. 
</P>
</TEXT>
