<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Flag, Emblem Bills Published In Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, May 2 (Xinhua) -- The Chief Executive' Office of the
Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (HKSAR) today published
two bills that give legal protection to the national and regional
flags and emblems.
</P>
<P>
The National Flag and National Emblem Bill and the Regional
Flag and Regional Emblem Bill give specifications for the use,
color and dimensions of the flags and emblems.
</P>
<P>
The two bills will be tabled to the Provisional Legislative
Council of HKSAR for consideration in Shenzhen, the Chinese city
bordering Hong Kong tomorrow.
</P>
<P>
Under the proposed legislation, the national flag, the national
emblem or both must be displayed at main government buildings. The
Chief Executive is empowered to stipulate other organizations and
places which must use or display the national and regional flags
and emblems.
</P>
<P>
The bills also provide that the flags and emblems should be
respected and cherished, and that none of them may be used in
trademarks or advertising. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970502.0068 </DOCNO>
