<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Seizes Record High Pirated Laser Disc </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, May 2 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong Custom seized 116,000
pieces of pirated laser disc, the largest number ever captured, in
a raid upon a local factory.
</P>
<P>
Custom officers searched a workshop in the New Territory
Thursday and found the big batch of pirated disc, estimated to be
4.6 million HK dollars (590,000 US dollars).
</P>
<P>
The pirated products were shipped into Hong Kong for sale, said
a Custom officer.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong custom launched more than 1,000 actions last year to
crack down on piracy and infringement on intellectual property
right. The confiscated laser disc amounted to one million pieces,
with a market value of 47 million HK dollars (6 million US
dollars).  
</P>
</TEXT>
