</P>
<P>
-- Last-minute disputes over tax cuts kept the White House and
republican leaders from closing a historic agreement to balance
the budget by 2002, extract deep savings in Medicare and provide a
net tax cut of 85 billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
-- After climbing steadily for more than two decades, sexual
activity among American teenagers has declined, the first drop
since the federal government began tracking the information in
1970, according to a new government survey released Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The New York Times:
</P>
<P>
-- The Justice Department said the Immigration and
Naturalization Service was falling further behind in processing
the record number of immigrants seeking citizenship.
</P>
<P>
