margin in Britain's national election, ending 18 years of
conservative rule.
</P>
<P>
The Wall Street Journal:
</P>
<P>
-- The Senate Commerce panel approved a measure that would cap
product-liability damage awards and set other limits in injury
suits, launching a Republican effort to revive the issue after
Clinton vetoed a similar bill last year. Separately, the Senate,
99-1, passed a bill to shield volunteers from liability lawsuits.
</P>
<P>
-- Yeltsin urged the U.S. to give "concrete meaning" to
assurances given in Helsinki that the planned expansion of NATO
into former Warsaw Pact nations won't threaten Russia. Secretary
of State Madeleine Albright met with her Russian counterpart in
Moscow, but made little progress on a charter allowing Russia
consultations with NATO. 
</P>
