<HEADLINE> Chinese Specialists with Foreign Credentials, Now A New Force in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, May 2 (Xinhua) -- With the growing economic bond
between Hong Kong and the mainland, a new breed of management
executives with both China background and internationally
accredited academic credentials is being nurtured.
</P>
<P>
The HR Education Group of Hong Kong disclosed today that about
90 percent of its students taking the Murdoch MBA Program taught
in Chinese have Chinese mainland background. The fact highlights
the formation of a new pool of China specialists in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Australia's Murdoch University and the HR Group jointly offered
the first MBA program with China components in 1995.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a press conference here today, Dean of the Business
School at Murdoch University Alan G. Davison said, "With the
impending handover of Hong Kong back to China, a stream of
management talents from the People's Republic of China are finding
their ways into the Hong Kong business community."
</P>
<P>
"Armed with an in-depth knowledge of the PRC's political and
economic environments and with worldwide recognized academic
credentials, these China specialists are popular recruits for Hong
Kong companies, particularly mainland corporations based here.
Their growing number is having an increasing impact on Hong Kong's
business world," he said.
</P>
<P>
Key Hong Kong business sectors, including finance and banking,
manufacturing and construction, trading and retailing, are
competing to recruit these executives for senior management
positions.
</P>
<P>
So far Murdoch's MBA programs in Hong Kong have recruited over
230 students.  
</P>
</TEXT>
