<HEADLINE> Glaxo Wellcome Builds Plant in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SUZHOU, May 2 (Xinhua) -- Glaxo Wellcome, the world's largest
medicine manufacturer, is to build a large pharmaceutical plant in
this city in east China's Jiangsu Province, according to an
agreement signed today.
</P>
<P>
The plant will be built on a plot of 7.2 ha in the Suzhou
Industrial Park, a three-year-old economic zone jointly developed
by China and Singapore.
</P>
<P>
In addition to the Glaxo Wellcome deal, another 12 agreements
for investment in the park were signed today by companies involved
in electronics, medicine, precision engineering and packaging from
North America, Europe, Japan, Singapore and China.
</P>
<P>
The agreed projects involve more than 200 million US dollars
in investment, which have raised to over three billion US dollars the
total amount of investment in the park.
</P>
<P>
Sip Hi-tech Development Co. Ltd. today became the first Chinese
enterprise to promise to invest in the park. It will invest 3.6
million US dollars in telecommunications equipment.
</P>
<P>
More than 90 companies have been set up in the park so far,
with 36 already operational and another 24 expected to begin
production by the year's end.
</P>
<P>
Once operational, the companies will create a total of 18,000
job opportunities, experts say.  
</P>
</TEXT>
