<HEADLINE> Angolan President Meets with Zairean Rebel Leader </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, May 2 (Xinhua) -- Angolan President Eduardo Dos
Santos today met with Zairean rebel leader Laurent-desire
Kabila at the state house and exchanged views with him on the
Zairean situation.
</P>
<P>
Kabila arrived here this morning from Lubumbashi and will
leave for a South African naval ship anchoring on the
international waters off Ponta Negra port of Congo to have
face-to-face talks with Zairean President Mobutu Sese Seko.
</P>
<P>
Both President Dos Santos and Laurent Kabila made no
disclosures to the press about their talks. However, observers
hold that the most important issue they discussed was Zairean
crisis.
</P>
<P>
President Dos Santos has recently expressed on various
occasions that Zairean conflict could be solved through
negotiations, and if necessary, he is willing to mediate.
</P>
</TEXT>
