<HEADLINE> Ramos to Make Special Pitch for Mindanao's Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, May 2 (Xinhua) -- President Fidel Ramos would make a
special pitch for Mindanao, the southern Philippines, to foreign
investors during his forthcoming visit to the United States,
Mexico and Panama beginning May 6.
</P>
<P>
In a briefing at the Presidential Palace today, Ramos urged the
members of his delegation to make extra efforts in bringing to the
foreign investors' attention the latest positive development in
Mindanao.
</P>
<P>
A lot of investment opportunities in Mindanao await businessmen
because of the enhanced peace and order situation and the
formation of several economic growth centers there, the president
said.
</P>
<P>
The government and the Moro National Liberation Front signed a
peace agreement last September, bringing to an end a 24-year-old
war which seriously damaged the economic development there.
</P>
<P>
Ramos also pointed out that foreign investors must be made
aware of Mindanao's large unexpected resources that could be
developed for the mutual benefits of the country and the
investors.
</P>
<P>
He assured joint ventures in the South will gain profits
because of the booming East ASEAN (Association of Southeast Asian
Nations) Growth Area, which is composed of Brunei and parts of
Indonesia, Malaysia and the Philippines.
</P>
<P>
The ASEAN also includes Singapore, Thailand and Vietnam besides
the four countries mentioned above.
</P>
<P>
Together with President Ramos in the trip are First Lady
Amelita Ramos, three cabinet members, six lawmakers and some 86
businessmen.  
</P>
</TEXT>
