<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Philippines to Host ASEAN Meeting on Agriculture </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, May 2 (Xinhua) -- Senior officials of the Association
of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN) will meet next week in the
Philippines to advance the development of agriculture and forestry
in the region.
</P>
<P>
The meeting, to be held on May 6-8 in Cebu, the second biggest
city in the country, will tackle issues including trade and
investments for agriculture, food security and handling, specific
concerns on crops, fishery and livestock and agricultural
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The major thrusts of the meeting is to strengthen the mechanism
for ASEAN's cooperation in agriculture and forestry to enhance the
ASEAN economies' competitiveness in the global market.
</P>
<P>
The meeting is also expected to spark a more active
participation of the private sector in various ASEAN growth areas
which include the Indonesia-Malaysia-Thailand Growth Triangle, the
Brunei-Indonesia-Malaysia-the Philippines East ASEAN Growth Area
and lately, the Mekong Basin Development Project.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, Manila will try to gain support of its
ASEAN partners for issues affecting the country's agricultural
exports such as the Philippines' concerns on desiccated coconut
exports to Brazil.  
</P>
</TEXT>
