<HEADLINE> HK Property Sales Surge in April </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, May 2 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong's property transactions
in April were more than those in any previous months, with the
number of deals surging 57 percent to some 25,300 and a total
value of 106 billion HK dollars (13.59 billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Today's South China Morning Post reported that the figures,
estimated by estate agents, exceeded the highest monthly record of
20,910 deals registered in October 1991 and 20,600 deals in April
1991.
</P>
<P>
The substantial increase in registration values was attributed
to the pre-sale of several big developments while two-thirds came
from government-subsidized Home Ownership Scheme projects, the
report said.
</P>
<P>
Estate agents forecast that May transaction volume figures
would fall sharply as a result of the market's abrupt correction
following government moves to stifle speculation.  
</P>
</TEXT>
