<DATE_TIME> 1997-05-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK Company to Show Autopass System in Mainland </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, May 2 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong's Cross-Harbor Tunnel
Co. plans to demonstrate in Beijing its Autopass system for
vehicles passing through tolls in a bid to expand its mainland
operations, according to today's South China Morning Post.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for the company was quoted as saying the trials
would begin in Beijing soon and they were also likely to be held
in other gateway cities including Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
Autopass users have a tag attached to their car that is scanned
automatically by a computer as they pass through a toll. The user
is billed without slowing down or stopping the vehicle.
</P>
<P>
In Hong Kong the system is used in 22 auto-toll lanes in five
tunnels. At the end of last year Autopass had nearly 87,000
vehicle users in Hong Kong.  
</P>
</TEXT>
