<HEADLINE> European Parliament Delegation to Visit Pakistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, May 2 (Xinhua) -- A four-member delegation of the
European Parliament will visit Pakistan this week to participate
in the third European Parliament-Pakistan Interparliamentary
Meeting.
</P>
<P>
The delegation led by Anita Pollack (UK), Chairperson of the
South Asia Delegation of the European Parliament, will be in
Pakistan for one week beginning from May 3.
</P>
<P>
During its stay here, the delegation will have extensive talks
with members of the National Assembly and Senators.
</P>
<P>
They will also call on President Farooq Leghari, Prime Minister
Nawaz Sharif, the Speaker of the National Assembly and the
Chairman of the Senate as well as other high-ranking government
officials, according to a press release today by the Delegation of
the European Commission to Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
The visit will also take them to Lahore, capital of Punjab
province, and the southern port city of Karachi, where they will
have contacts with the provincial governments and assemblies, and
also with business and representatives of the non-governmental
organizations.
</P>
<P>
The first European Parliament-Pakistan Interparliamentary
Meeting was held in Islamabad in 1991, and the second was held in
Strasbourg, France, in 1993.  
</P>
</TEXT>
