<HEADLINE> Bills, Transitional Budget to Be Tabled to PLC </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, May 2 (Xinhua) -- Another two draft bills, together
with the transitional budget for Hong Kong, will be tabled to the
Provisional Legislative Council (PLC) at its full sitting in
Shenzhen tomorrow.
</P>
<P>
The two bills to be presented by the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (HKSAR) Chief Executive's Office are the
National Flag and National Emblem Bill and the Regional Flag and
Regional Emblem Bill.
</P>
<P>
Three weeks ago the office tabled the first bill, namely the
Holidays (1997 and 1998) Bill, to the PLC for first and second
readings.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the director of the office will move a motion on the
transitional budget at the meeting.
</P>
<P>
The 1997-1998 budget needs examination and approval of both the
Legislative Council, whose mission ends midnight June 30, and the
PLC since the budget covers three months before the handover and
nine months after the handover.
</P>
<P>
Another motion is expected to be moved by Selina Chow, convenor
of the Rules of Procedure Working Group, on the adoption of the
English version of the rules of procedure of the PLC.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese version, together with two amendments to it, has
already been adopted. 
</P>
</TEXT>
