<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Macao Birth Rate Drops </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, May 2 (Xinhua) -- The birth rate in Macao has dropped
for eight consecutive years, with 5,468 babies born in 1996, down
6.9 percent from the previous year.
</P>
<P>
Latest figures released by the Macao Census and Statistics
Department show that 1,413 deaths were recorded last year, up 4.6
percent. The three leading killer diseases were of circulatory
system, of tumor and of respiratory system.
</P>
<P>
In addition, a total of 2,106 couples wedded in 1996, down 1.9
percent. The average age of the first-married bride was 28.3 years
old, and for bridegroom 31.4 years old.
</P>
<P>
Macao's permanent population reached 414,000 last year, with
the average population growth rate dropping to about 3 percent
since 1990.
</P>
<P>
Besides the natural growth of population, the immigration of
foreign nationals is also slowing down.
</P>
<P>
Last year, a total of 1,465 foreign nationals and 1,857
one-way-permit holders from Chinese mainland were permitted to
move into Macao. Most foreign nationals came from Asia.
</P>
<P>
By the end of 1996, there were 22,636 foreign nationals living
in the territory, whose land area added up to some 21 square
kilometers.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Macao repatriated 6,875 illegal immigrants in 1996,
75.9 percent of them female. The figure was 4.3 percent more than
in 1995.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
