<DOCNO> XIE19970502.0107 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-05-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Australian Dollar Ends Weaker by Lower Interest Rates </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, May 2 (Xinhua) -- The Australian dollar closed weaker
today, pushed down at the beginning of the session by calls from
Prime Minister John Howard for lower interest rates.
</P>
<P>
Howard said over radio that "our real interest rates are too
high, we still don't have enough competition for small business
finance within the banking system."
</P>
<P>
The Australian dollar closed 78.32 US cents from 78.45 US cents
at the close Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The foreign exchange market is now waiting for the US labor
data, due out tonight, economists have forecast that non-farm
payrolls rose by 210,000 jobs in April, and the unemployment rate
is expected to be unchanged at 5.2 percent.
</P>
<P>
On the cross-rates, the Australian dollar closed weaker, it
ended at 99.27 yen from 99.95 yen against the Japanese yen, and
was at 1.3488 marks from 1.3591 marks against the German mark.
</P>
</TEXT>
