<HEADLINE> HK to Issue Special Stamps on Modern Buildings </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, May 2 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong is to issue a set of
special stamps on the theme of the Hong Kong Modern Landmarks on
May 18, which will be the last special stamp issue under British
rule, announced Robert Footman, the postmaster general of Hong
Kong.
</P>
<P>
Footman said the special stamp issue features four modern
landmarks in Hong Kong. There will be four denominations --
1.30HKD (the Hong Kong Stadium), 2.50HKD (the Peak Tower), 3.10HKD
(the Hong Kong Convention and Exhibition Center) and 5HKD (the
Lantau Link).
</P>
<P>
The stamp sheets do not have any numbering on the edges. A
stamp sheetlet incorporating the 5HKD stamp will also be
introduced. This is the first ever stamp sheetlet issued in Hong
Kong applying gold foiling technique.
</P>
<P>
After Hong Kong's return to China on July 1, 1997, stamps
bearing the Queen's portrait or "Royal Cypher" will not be valid
for the payment of postage. They can be exchanged for an
equivalent value of the definitive stamps from July 3-31,
1997.  
</P>
</TEXT>
