<HEADLINE> OAU Seeks End to Zairean Crisis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, May 2 (Xinhua) -- Zaire deserves a better deal through
negotiated political transition and an end to anarchy,
Organization of African Unity Secretary-General Salim Ahmed Salim
said here Thursday night.
</P>
<P>
"It is important to put an end to the war and negotiate a
transition that will create a new order in Zaire," said Salim who
arrived here to attend the Summit of African First Ladies on
Peace scheduled for May 5-7 in Abuja, the Nigerian capital.
</P>
<P>
Despite acknowledging that the Zairean rebels, led by Laurent
Kabila, have a military advantage over President Mobutu's force,
Kabila stressed that it was only by peace talks that the crisis
could be best resolved.
</P>
<P>
The OAU secretary-general said he believed that African women,
through mobilization and effort of the first ladies, could
contribute meaningfully towards resolving various social problems
emanating from the crisis in their countries, particularly the
problems of war refugees.
</P>
<P>
More than 40 African countries have indicated their desire to
participate in the summit and about 30 first ladies will lead
official delegations to the conference. 
</P>
</TEXT>
