<HEADLINE> GPC Wins Majority of Votes in Parliamentary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANAA, May 2 (Xinhua) -- The Yemeni General People's Congress
(GPC) party has won in 183 of the total 301 constituencies in the
ongoing parliamentary elections, according to an announcement by
the country's electoral committee.
</P>
<P>
The preliminary ballot counting, which involved 286 electoral
constituencies out of a total of 301 in the country, had been
completed by midnight Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The principal operations room of the Yemeni supreme electoral
committee announced that the GPC won 183 seats, and the Islamic
Gathering for Reform (IGR), one of the coalition ruling parites
with the GPC, got 47 seats and independent candidates gained 51
seats.
</P>
<P>
Besides, the Nasserist Unionist Organization won three seats
and the Baath Arab Socialist Party two seats. Ballot counting had
been underway until midnight Thursday in 14 electoral
constituencies.
</P>
<P>
The supreme electoral committee decided that elections in
electoral constituency 204 in the Zamar governorate would be
re-held at a later date.
</P>
<P>
Ballot counting is due to be completed later today in all of
the 301 electoral constituencies, and the final results would be
announced by the supreme election committee.
</P>
<P>
Parliamentary elections in the country began on April 27 under
the supervision of thousands of Yemeni and international
observers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
