<HEADLINE> Fasih Bokhari Appointed Pakistan's Naval Chief </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, May 2 (Xinhua) -- Vice Admiral Fasih Bokhari has
been appointed as Pakistan's chief of naval staff with immediate
effect, sources from the Defense Ministry said Thursday in
Rawalpindi, a twin city of Islamabad.
</P>
<P>
Fasih Bokhari assumed the post a week after his predecessor,
Admiral Mansurul Haq, resigned in the wake of widespread
accusation of alleged corruption leveled against him.
</P>
<P>
Fasih Bokhari, who joined the navy on January 1, 1959, and
graduated from the French Naval War College in 1975, has held
numerous key staff and command appointments both ashore and afloat
during his 38 years of service.
</P>
<P>
He joined the Submarine Service in 1964 and was part of the
acquisition crew of the Daphne class submarines.
</P>
<P>
He has commanded a Daphne submarine and has had two tours of
duty of Destroyer Command. He has been commander of submarines,
director of naval operations and director of naval warfare
operation plans.
</P>
<P>
He has also served as deputy chief of naval staff (supply) at
the Naval Headquarters.  
</P>
</TEXT>
