<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Peng Zhen's Glorious, militant life (14) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Comrade Peng Zhen for a long time presided over the work of the
NPC Standing committee, and made painstaking efforts to establish
and improve the system of people's congress. As early as in 1951,
he pointed out that "the system of the people congress is China's
fundamental political system, the basic organizational form for
the whole people to run the country, and the best, most effective,
and most important form for us to follow the mass line in work
concerning political power."
</P>
<P>
During the new historical period, he put forward the principle
that the people take the future and destiny of the country of the
Chinese nation into their own hands through the system of the
people congress, and this is guarantee for people's fundamental
interests. It is also a reliable guarantee for China to withstand
various risks; The NPC Standing Committee, conducting its work in
accordance with responsibility entrusted by the Constitution,
should, first, not neglect its duty, and second, not overstep its
authority; It must, in the course of its work, strictly abide by
the principle of democratic centralism, exercise its power and
make decisions as a collective, seek unity of thought in the
process of developing a democratic style of work to the full, and
implement a high degree of centralism based on a high degree of
democracy; It must also continuously consolidate the building of
its organization and system to make its performance more
systematic and standardized step by step.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970502.0137 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-05-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Peng Zhen's Glorious, Militant Life (15) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Comrade Peng Zhen was in charge of the work of China's
political science and laws. He implemented the CPC Central
Committee's principles and policies in this regard in a creative
way and made significant contributions to establishing and
improving of the institutions, regulations and ranks of the legal
system, maintaining national security and social stability, and
guaranteeing a smooth progress of socialist construction.
</P>
<P>
After the Third Plenum of the 11th CPC Central Committee, he
devoted all his wisdom and energy to eliminating the grave evil
results caused by the "Great Cultural Revolution" which had
"smashed the systems of public security, procuratorate and court,"
and to rehabilitating, improving and strengthening the legal work
and contingent.
</P>
<P>
In 1980, he was appointed director of the Trial Guidance
Committee of the "two counter-revolutionary cases" of the Lin Biao
and Jiang Qing counter-revolutionary cliques and guided the trials
of the two cases. He secured the great success of the trials of
the two cases by determining a basic principle of "strict division
between the wrongdoings by a number of Party members and people
and the counter-revolutionary crimes," insisting on using facts as
the basis and laws as the criterion and acting strictly in
accordance with the law.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970502.0138 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-05-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Peng Zhen's Glorious, Militant Life (16) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
He summed up the historical experience of the work of political
science and law and made an overall exposition on the tasks,
principles, policies and contingent building of the work in the
new era. He pointed out: The fundamental tasks for the work in the
new era are: serve the socialist modernization drive under the
guidance of the four cardinal principles; crack down on the crimes
that severely jeopardize public order, and crimes that sabotage
the economy, firmly fight against criminal activities that
endanger the efforts to promote socialist cultural and ethical
progress, and ensure the smooth progress of reform, opening up and
the four modernizations drive; deal with the criminals who
seriously damage public order severely and promptly in accordance
with the law; educate, help and rehabilitate juvenile delinquents
in a compassionate, patient and meticulous way like parents
treating their children who contract epidemic diseases. He pointed
out: the work of the political science and law must be fully
dependent on the leadership of the Party, closely rely on the
masses of the people, combine the specialized organs with the mass
line, and oppose and overcome mysticism; great efforts must be
made to improve the political and professional proficiency of the
people working in political science and law.
</P>
</TEXT>
