<DOCNO> XIE19970502.0139 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-05-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Peng Zhen's Glorious, Militant Life (17) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Comrade Peng Zhen, on behalf of the Party and the state, met
with friends and comrades from many countries, visited many
countries and participated many times in conferences and talks on
vital issues concerning the international Communist movement.
</P>
<P>
In activities involving foreign affairs he adhered to the basic
principle of the Party and the state on handling party-to-party
and country-to-country relations, staunchly upheld the independent
principled stand of the Communist Party of China, and made
outstanding contributions to safeguarding the dignity and
interests of the country and the nation, promoting friendship
between the Chinese people and other people of other countries,
and promoting the cause of world peace and humanity progress.
</P>
<P>
After his retirement in 1988, Comrade Peng Zhen was aways
concerned about the country's reform, opening up and the socialist
modernization drive. During the political incident between spring
and summer in 1989, he made an important speech on "Using the
Constitution and Laws to Unify our Thinking", which played a
significant role in unifying the people's thinking, educating the
people, distinguishing between the right and the wrong, and
safeguarding the independence, dignity, security and stability of
the country.
</P>
