<DOCNO> XIE19970502.0140 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-05-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Peng Zhen's Glorious, Militant Life (18) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
He resolutely supported the central collective leadership with
Comrade Jiang Zemin at the core, highly praised the important
speech that Comrade Deng Xiaoping made during his south China
inspection tour in early 1992 and the spirit of the plenary
meeting of the Political Bureau of the CPC Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
He said that Comrade Deng Xiaoping had stated that adherence to
"one central task and two basic points" (taking economic
development as the central task and upholding reform and opening
up policy and the four cardinal principles) is the basic line of
the Party. The Party must concentrate on achieving faster and
better economic development, carry forward the fine tradition of
the Party, and place equal stress on the development of both
material progress and cultural and ethical progress.
</P>
<P>
Since reform and opening to the outside world are intended to
develop and emancipate social productive forces, it is imperative
to adhere to to them till the realization of communism.
</P>
<P>
In the past decade, despite his advanced age, Comrade Peng Zhen
spent all his energy reading books, newspapers and documents and
making investigations. He was concerned about state-run
enterprises, agriculture, rural work and the building of the
Party, as well as the future and destiny of the Party and the
country. He also followed closely the changes in the international
arena.
</P>
<P>
Because of over-fatigue, he was struck by sudden severe
illnesses in April 1991 and September 1992. With an iron will, he
staunchly fought against his illness and conquered it twice, thus
performing a miracle.
</P>
<P>
The CPC Central Committee with Comrade Jiang Zemin at the core
showed great concern for Comrade Peng Zhen, who earnestly put
forward suggestions to the Party's Central Committee, firmly
supported its work and highly praised the achievements that have
been made since the 14th Party National Congress.
</P>
</TEXT>
