<DATE_TIME> 1997-05-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Peng Zhen's Glorious, Militant Life (19) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In January 1991 the Literature Editorial Committee of the CPC
Central Committee edited and published the "Selected Works of Peng
Zhen". His three works, namely, "On Socialist Democracy and
Building of Legal System in the New Period", "Standing in the
Forefront of Revolution and Construction" and "On the Work of
Political Science and Law In New China," were also been published.
</P>
<P>
In his 70-odd-year revolutionary career Comrade Peng Zhen has a
firm conviction in communism, was boundlessly loyal to the Party,
the People and the revolutionary cause of the proletariat,
undaunted by repeated setbacks, and firm and indomitable.
</P>
<P>
He indefatigably studied Marxism, persisted in linking theory
with practice, did a good job in applying Marxist stand,
viewpoints and methods to acutely discover problems and analyze
and resolve them realistically, thereby demonstrating the courage
and resourcefulness and organizational ability of a revolutionary
in creatively creating a new situation and dealing with complex
problems.
</P>
<P>
At the critical moments and on the vital issues that had a
bearing on the future and destiny of the Party and State, Peng
Zhen always adhered to principles. He unswervingly persisted in
the purpose of serving the people wholeheartedly, based his code
of conduct on the greatest interests of the greatest majority of
people, and always maintained the true qualities as a public
servant of the people.
</P>
<P>
He adhered to the principle of democratic centralism, the
collective leadership of the Party and the mass line. He went deep
into the realities of life, made investigations and studies and
had a democratic work style. He was keen on hearing different
opinions and pooling the wisdom of the masses and was resourceful
and decisive. He was modest and prudent, sincere, honest and
strict with himself.
</P>
<P>
He upheld the truth and was ready to correct his mistakes
immediately. He was open and above-board, took the interests of
the whole into account, and was a model in observing the
discipline of the Party.
</P>
<P>
He cared about other comrades and cadres, respected knowledge
and talented people, and trained a large number of leading
cadres for the cause of the Party.
</P>
<P>
Comrade Peng Zhen proved himself to be a proletarian
revolutionary of the old generation who enjoyed high prestige and
commanded universal respect, performed outstanding feats, won the
love and esteem of the whole Party and people of all ethnic groups
throughout the country.
</P>
<P>
Comrade Peng Zhen historical feats for China's revolution and
socialist construction will go down in history forever. His
revolutionary spirit and noble qualities have set an example for
the whole Party and the people of all ethnic groups all over the
country to follow.
</P>
<P>
Comrade Peng Zeng will live in the heart of the people forever!
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
