<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0800 GMT, May 2 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA -- Senior officials from the ASEAN ministries of
agriculture and forestry will hold a special meeting in the
southern Philippine city of Cebu next week, the Philippine News
Agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
NEW DELHI -- India has expressed regret at the
U.S. decision to continue to place it on a "priority watch list"
under the U.S. "Special 301" trade law provisions.
</P>
<P>
JAKARTA -- Indonesia will probably face Japan's second
complaint to the panel of the World Trade Organization after the
country rejected the suit, an official said.
</P>
<P>
TIRANA -- Albanian Prime Minister Bashkim Fino warned Thursday
that his government will resign if the parliament fails to pass
the election law.
</P>
<P>
LONDON -- Britain's Labor Party has won 330 seats in the
election, enough to form a new government and its leader Tony
Blair will be Britain's Prime Minister, according to the initial
result announced today. 
</P>
