<HEADLINE> Carl Lewis Skips Osaka Grand Prix </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, May 2 (Xinhua) -- American athletics legend Carl Lewis
has decided to skip the IAAF Japanese Grand Prix in Osaka next
week, organizers said on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Lewis, winner of nine Olympic gold medals, had injuried his
Achilles' tendon two weeks ago in California, the organizers said.
</P>
<P>
Originally, Lewis was scheduled to compete in the 100 meters
wherein he sprinted to a then world mark of 9.86 at the World
Championships in Tokyo.
</P>
<P>
However, his compatriot Leroy Burrell, also former world 100m
record holder of 9.85sec, will replaced Lewis, the organizers said.
</P>
<P>
The Osaka grand prix is the second of the 18-round grand prix
series with the final slated in Fukuoka on September 13. 
</P>
</TEXT>
