<HEADLINE> Kenya to Undertake Export Promotion Program </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, May 2 (Xinhua) -- The Kenya Association of
Manufacturers (KAM) is scheduled to implement an Export Promotion
Program for the next two years.
</P>
<P>
Local paper the Daily Nation today quoted KAM Chief Executive
Z. Kahura as saying that the program would focus on
non-traditional, especially agricultural products.
</P>
<P>
KAM has been organizing workshops in Nairobi and Eldoret to
sensitize the public on the benefits of the program and one more
workshop was scheduled to be held in the southern port city of
Mombasa next month.
</P>
<P>
The program is aimed at helping agricultural sector increase
food production by fostering linkages between the sector and the
agro-processing, food processing and related sub-sectors.
</P>
<P>
The program will also assist related sectors in improving
quality, design and presentation of their products for specific
markets, said the KAM official.
</P>
<P>
The strategies for reducing costs to enhance competitiveness
will also be addressed by the program which will be implemented
on a 50 percent cost sharing basis between the companies being
assisted and the program, he noted.
</P>
<P>
The program will be restricted to private companies and KAM
will be in charge of the implementation through the cooperation
with the members. 
</P>
</TEXT>
