<HEADLINE> Philippines to Host ASEAN Agriculture Meeting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, May 2 (Xinhua) -- Senior officials from the ASEAN
ministries of agriculture and forestry will hold a special meeting
in the southern Philippine city of Cebu next week, the Philippine
News Agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
The meeting scheduled on May 6-8 will follow up the progress of
sectoral cooperation to advance ASEAN common interests in
agriculture and forestry, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The ASEAN!!(Association of Southeast Asian Nations) now groups
Brunei, Indonesia, Malaysia, the Philippines, Singapore, Thailand
and Vietnam.
</P>
<P>
The meeting is expected to tackle issues such as trade and
investments for agriculture, food security and handling, specific
concerns on crops, fisheries and livestock, agricultural extension
and training and agricultural cooperatives, the report said.
</P>
<P>
It said the meeting will strengthen the mechanism for ASEAN
cooperation in pooling resources, networking, complementation of
industries and sharing of markets to hasten growth and enhance
competitiveness of the ASEAN economies on the global market.
</P>
<P>
The meeting is also expected to spark a more active
participation of the private sector in various ASEAN growth areas,
it said.
</P>
<P>
These areas include the Indonesia-Malaysia-Thailand Growth
Triangle, the Singapore-Johore-Riau Growth Triangle, the Brunei
Darussalam-Indonesia-Malaysia-the Philippines East ASEAN Growth
Area, and the Mekong Basin Development Project.  
</P>
</TEXT>
