<HEADLINE> Fake Kenya Notes Found in E. Uganda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, May 2 (Xinhua) -- A large amount of counterfeit
Kenyan local currency notes have been found around eastern
Uganda's border region during the last several weeks.
</P>
<P>
Local daily the New Vision said today that the notes were
mainly in the denominations of 1,000 Kenyan shillings (about two
U.S. Dollars) and 500 Shillings bearing the portrait of Kenyan
President Daniel arap Moi.
</P>
<P>
In Jinja, a town 80 km east of capital Kampala, a local
resident said in two days this week, he received 6,000 Kenyan
shillings of counterfeit notes.
</P>
<P>
Traders around the border areas have been warned by the police
to make sure they exchange their money at foreign exchange
bureaus or at least they should be careful when dealing with
money vendors.
</P>
<P>
The counterfeit dealers target mainly those dealing in Kenyan
merchandise, local police said. 
</P>
