announced here today.
</P>
<P>
Abu Hassan is in replacement of Muhammad Muhamad Taib, who
resigned on April 14 after facing two charges in Australia in
connection with his failure to declare the equivalent of 2.4
million ringgit (about 0.96 million U.S. dollars) while leaving
