<HEADLINE> Fuel Prices Rise in Zimbabwe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, May 2 (Xinhua) -- The prices of petrol, diesel and
other petroleum products went up as of mid-night yesterday by
between 12 and 24 percent, three months after the last increase.
</P>
<P>
In what now appears to be a quarterly increase, with the last
two coming in October 1996 and January this year, the Zimbabwe
government said several factors, including the depreciation of
the Zimbabwe Dollar and the political tension in the Middle East,
had necessitated the hike.
</P>
<P>
The government also blamed the current level of inflation for
the increase, saying it had had a negative effect on oil company
performances. 
