<HEADLINE> Albanian Parliament Urged to Ratify Election Law </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, May 1 (Xinhua) -- Albanian Prime Minister Bashkim Fino
warned today that his government will have to resign if the
parliament fails to pass the election law.
</P>
<P>
In a meeting with visiting European Union (EU) special envoy
Franz Vranitzky, former Austrian prime minister, Fino said that if
the Democrats-dominated parliament does not ratify the bill, his
government will soon face a crisis and Albania will fall back into
anarchy.
</P>
<P>
This is the first time Fino has warned that his all-party
interim government may resign.
</P>
<P>
He asked Vranitzky to help mediate between the Democrats and
the nine parties for a peaceful Albania.
</P>
<P>
Conflicts between Socialists led by Prime Minister Fino and
Democrats led by President Sali Berisha are increasingly tense
when the general election date of June 29 is approaching.
</P>
<P>
The prime minister also urged the 6,000-strong Italian-led
multinational force to guard arms depots and other military
facilities. A Tuesday blast at an arms depot killed 27 people.
</P>
<P>
More than 400 people have been killed since the nation was
engulfed by riots in January over the collapse of fraudulent
investment funds. Most of the arms depots were looted by armed
protesters. 
</P>
