<HEADLINE> Cuba Marks May Day With Big Parade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, May 1 (Xinhua) -- About 1 million Cubans held a march
here today to mark May Day, the International Labor Day.
</P>
<P>
The march, presided over by President Fidel Castro, was
characterized by a strong popular rejection of the policy of
increasing hostility of the United States toward the island.
</P>
<P>
The celebration was dedicated to the 30th anniversary of the
death of the legendary Cuban-Argentine guerrilla leader, Ernesto
"Che" Guevara, who died in 1967 in a combat in Bolivia.
</P>
<P>
