of the Cuban Workers Central Organization Pedro Ross delivered a
short speech reaffirming the will of the workers and of all Cubans
to defend the motherland and socialism.
</P>
<P>
He said there cannot be agreements with the powerful northern
neighbor if there is no respect for the independence and
sovereignty of the nation.
</P>
<P>
The march was started at 9 a.m. (local time) by 34 National
Vanguard centers accompanied by a group of construction workers.
</P>
<P>
The demonstrators held placards and posters condemning the
U.S. government and its plans to intensify the embargo against
Cuba through the Helms-Burton law. 
</P>
