<HEADLINE> Xu Reelected as Table Tennis Chief </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANCHESTER, England, May 1 (Xinhua) -- Xu Yinsheng was
reelected as president of the International Table Tennis
Federation (ITTF) in the ITTF Biennial General Meeting here on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Xu, Chinese former world champion who took the ITTF top seat
after former president Lollo Hammarlund died of lung cancer in
1995, was the only one nominated for this position.
</P>
<P>
Adam Sharara, general secretary of the Canadian table tennis
association, was elected as the ITTF deputy president.
</P>
<P>
The meeting vetoed a resolution that world championships be
seperated into team and individual events.
</P>
<P>
The ITTF Athletes Commission had proposed that the world
championships be held annually with team events in even years and
individual events in odd years.
</P>
<P>
The meeting also rejected a proposal to change the service
rule, giving an OK to these players who partly hide the ball while
serving.
</P>
<P>
This proposal suggested that in service the ball be struck
between the front of the service body and his end line. At
present, the ball can be partly hidden by the body of the server.
</P>
</TEXT>
