<HEADLINE> UK Shares End Election Day at Record Close </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, May 1 (Xinhua) -- British shares on the London stock
market ended the session at a new closing high although trading
volumes were thin on a nervous election day while markets in both
Frankfurt and Paris closed for the May Day holiday.
</P>
<P>
The FTSE 100 index finished 9.0 points higher at a new record
close of 4,445.0 points, although only 0.7 points above the
previous closing record of 4,444.3 reached on March 11.
</P>
<P>
However, trading volumes were moderate as many institutional
investors stayed away ahead of the UK general election result, due
out early Friday morning.
</P>
<P>
A marginally stronger-than-expected UK purchasing managers'
report earlier today had little impact on trade, dealers said.
</P>
